thane — AI-native terminal workspace manager
=============================================

Quick install
-------------

  ./install.sh

This installs the binaries, desktop entry, and icon. It will prompt for
sudo to copy binaries to /usr/local/bin and install runtime dependencies
if needed.

Manual install
--------------

1. Install runtime dependencies (Ubuntu/Debian):

     sudo apt install libgtk-4-1 libvte-2.91-gtk4-0 libwebkitgtk-6.0-4

   Fedora:

     sudo dnf install gtk4 vte291-gtk4 webkitgtk6.0

2. Copy binaries:

     sudo install -m 755 thane /usr/local/bin/thane
     sudo install -m 755 thane-cli /usr/local/bin/thane-cli

3. (Optional) Install desktop entry and icon:

     cp com.thane.app.desktop ~/.local/share/applications/
     mkdir -p ~/.local/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps
     cp com.thane.app.svg ~/.local/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/

4. Launch:

     thane

Uninstall
---------

  sudo rm /usr/local/bin/thane /usr/local/bin/thane-cli
  rm ~/.local/share/applications/com.thane.app.desktop
  rm ~/.local/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/com.thane.app.svg

Documentation:  https://getthane.com/docs
Contact:        https://getthane.com/contact
